description._content:
Fourth page of a printed constitution for the Women Citizens' League of Deseronto, Ontario.

"COMMITTEES
The standing committees shall be as follows:
Local Improvement - to endeavor to improve the appearance of the town.
Charity and Health - to render assistance wherever necessary and to work with the Municipal Charity Committee in the relief of cases of need.
Entertainment - to provide for the reading of a paper of some form of entertainment at each monthly meeting. To suggest ways and means of raising funds and with the help of all the members carry out any entertainment decided upon.
Property - to be responsible for the upkeep of all properties owned by the League.

AMENDMENTS:
The Constitution and By-laws may be amended by a two-thirds vote, notice of such change having been given in writing at a previous meeting.
The rules of parliamentary practice shall govern the proceedings of the League, subject to any special rules that may be adopted."

One of a number of items which originally belonged to Cecil and Elizabeth Argue of Deseronto, Ontario. Donated to the Archives in October 2013.
